720.question: How much is proposed model better than baselines in performed experiments?
720.response: {'Answer': 'The GDP model performs the best among the baselines in terms of BPRA and BLEU scores in the DSTC2 and Maluuba datasets. The addition of reinforcement learning (RL) further enhances its performance, making GDP+RL the most effective model with the highest BPRA and APRA scores, although it requires more training time.'}
720.answer:
most of the models have similar performance on BPRA: DSTC2 (+0.0015), Maluuba (+0.0729)
GDP achieves the best performance in APRA: DSTC2 (+0.2893), Maluuba (+0.2896)
GDP significantly outperforms the baselines on BLEU: DSTC2 (+0.0791), Maluuba (+0.0492)
